### 4.2 Enhanced Features (Phase 2)

#### 4.2.1 Advanced Block Reusability
**Priority:** P1 (High)

**Requirements:**
- Drag blocks directly from library into prompt builder
- Visual indication of library-sourced vs. custom blocks
- Block versioning (track changes over time)
- Block templates (pre-configured multi-block patterns)
- Tags and categories for organization
- Block performance tracking (which blocks in successful prompts)

#### 4.2.2 Template System
**Priority:** P1 (High)

**Requirements:**
- Pre-built prompt templates for common use cases:
  - Chain of Thought reasoning
  - Few-Shot learning
  - ReAct agent
  - Creative writing
  - Code generation
  - Data analysis
- Template marketplace (community templates)
- Template customization
- Template ratings and reviews
- One-click template instantiation

#### 4.2.3 Prompt Mixer
**Priority:** P1 (High)

**Requirements:**
- Select multiple prompts to combine
- Visual interface showing source prompts
- Intelligent merge suggestions from AI
- Conflict resolution for duplicate blocks
- Preview combined result
- Save as new prompt or template

#### 4.2.4 Collaboration Features
**Priority:** P2 (Medium)

**Requirements:**
- Share prompts via link (read-only or editable)
- Team workspaces
- Comment on blocks
- Version history with diff view
- Real-time collaborative editing
- Permission management

---

### 4.3 Advanced Features (Phase 3)

#### 4.3.1 Node-Based Prompt Builder
**Priority:** P2 (Medium)

**Requirements:**
- Alternative view mode for complex prompts
- Nodes represent blocks with input/output connectors
- Visual flow showing information dependencies
- Support for conditional logic
- Branch and merge patterns
- Export to linear prompt structure
- Library integration (React Flow)

**Use Cases:**
- Multi-agent systems
- Complex reasoning chains
- Conditional prompt flows
- Workflow visualization

#### 4.3.2 Prompt Testing & Analytics
**Priority:** P2 (Medium)

**Requirements:**
- Test prompts against multiple inputs
- Compare outputs from different prompt versions
- Track prompt performance metrics
- A/B testing framework
- Cost estimation (token usage)
- Response quality scoring

#### 4.3.3 Prompt Optimization
**Priority:** P2 (Medium)

**Requirements:**
- AI-suggested improvements
- Token optimization (reduce without losing effectiveness)
- Technique recommendations
- Anti-pattern detection
- Best practice checklist

#### 4.3.4 Knowledge Base / RAG Integration
**Priority:** P2 (Medium)

**Requirements:**
- Upload documentation for prompt context
- Semantic search across knowledge base
- Auto-suggest relevant context blocks
- Vector database for embeddings
- Document chunking and indexing

